This problem can be solved by topological sorting. We can use the degree of each node to sort them. In this problem, a team is stronger if it has an incoming edge. So we count the in-degree of each team, and return the team with in-degree 0. If there are multiple teams with in-degree 0, there is no unique champion, so we return -1.

public class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}

